<TITLE> Vietnam official shot in S Africa robbery </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 JOHANNESBURG, Oct 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A Vietnamese embassy official in South Africa was shot and wounded by armed robbers at his home in the capital Pretoria, police said on Sunday. Pretoria police spokesman Paul Ramaloko said five men, one armed with a pistol, attacked the man and his family on Saturday evening, SAPA news agency reported. "He was shot by the man armed with a pistol in the stomach. The men robbed him off his cell phone and a digital dictionary," he said. The man was taken to a local hospital, where he was in a serious but stable condition, SAPA reported. South Africa has one of the highest rates of violent crime in the world, and recent attacks on high-profile figures have sparked new calls for a crackdown on violent cri
